        "summary":  "Salesforce\u0027s acquisition of Informatica and subsequent integration of MDM, governance, and data quality capabilities into its AI platform reflects a market-wide shift: enterprise AI success now hinges on trusted, governed context rather than model quality. Salesforce\u0027s State of Data and Analytics research found 84% of data leaders believe their organizations need significant data strategy changes before AI can succeed at scale. The article argues agentic AI is exposing master data management problems that have existed for years.",
        "execSummary":  "The reframing of enterprise AI success as a data governance problem ΓÇö not a model problem ΓÇö is the defining strategic insight of this article, and it carries direct budget implications for every enterprise AI investment thesis. Agentic systems are surfacing duplicate records, inconsistent definitions, and broken data ownership at machine speed, turning what was once a background IT concern into a board-level blocker. For senior leaders, enterprise case studies illustrate that MDM investments that improve operational execution ΓÇö not just data quality scores ΓÇö are the ones that generate measurable AI ROI. The key caveat: combining governance complexity with platform simplicity is a hard product problem, and implementation timelines will reflect that difficulty.",
